story_txt:
Introduction Welcome to Antarra - a little mining planet on the outskirts of the Federation territories. Prepare to be amazed by a fantabulous show full of rivalry and competition for the title of the best pilot, the winner of which will be granted the honor of joining the elite squad of Federation pilots. Is there a better way to prove your worth than winning the biggest and the fastest race in this part of the universe? It will be the ultimate test of character, reflexes, resolve, technique and endurance (even against a direct rocket hit) for the best pilots this universe has ever known. In a series of races including time-trials, head-to-head competition and elimination on five different planets in various environments and different conditions a new champion will rise... 
 

  The Game Our game is all about space races - fast and spectacular! The tracks run through jungles, deserts, ruins of ancient civilizations and even the ocean floor! The game was inspired by old games such as Mega Race, Star Wars Racer or Wipeout. However, we are not trying to clone any of these games, we would like to follow their examples, but also to confront them with our own vision of the genre, our own solutions and ideas.  Here are some of the features you will see in the game (some of them are already finished):

Tracks - 5 completely different planets, varying in climate and environments. Some are ideal for high-speed laps, while others are planned for fierce competition and shortcut hunting;

Vehicles along with their parameters that can be tuned and modified freely (speed, handling, shields);

Weapons - there will be several types of those; some of the races will require the pilots to use them to be the first on the finish line;

Power-ups -depending on the race mode, you will see useful pick-up items along the track;

Leader - each planet will have its local champion - beat him to win his vehicle;

Soundtrack - we have a custom soundtrack recorded for the game, every song highlights the unique character of each planet;

Free DLCs - we are planning to make several free DLCs that will add new vehicles and planets.


 

  About us But let's get down to Earth, shall we? We are a team of two guys called Ambiverse who want to fulfill their dream and create something different... than we usually do. We have decided to join our forces, combine our knowledge and create something unique. We have set the bar quite high, but we felt it was the right thing to do. We have tested different things and solutions, gained new skills and finally decided to pick up this project. One year later...
 

  What are we raising the funds for? We have managed to finish most of the project by investing our own spare time, resources and skills. People often helped us just because they could - this is how we have received, for example, a license to use some of the fonts we needed. Eventually we hit a wall, a bigger technical issue, which has to be solved before we can release the title the way we want. We do not want to cut or resign from content we planned for the game, so after long talks and careful consideration of all our options, we are facing a critical choice - we can either hire one more person to help us polish the final product, or we can give up - which obviously is not an option. Unfortunately, our financial resources are limited and nobody (apart from us) will work for free. 
  Thresholds

1500€ - our main goal aims at hiring one more person to finish the game

2000€ - would let us add additional content such as new tracks or vehicles to the game

5000€ - would let us re-master the sounds and re-record them in a studio

10000€ - means we could hire additional people and add a multiplayer mode


  What platforms are we targeting? We dedicate our game to iOS with the target devices being iPhone 4 / iPod 4 / iPad 2 and better. UDK operates on these platforms with no additional extensions. We cannot guarantee ports into other platforms, but we are not ruling out ports into Android.
 

  How can you help? Everyone can help. You can donate, give positive comment or constructive criticism, share the link to our site or anything else, really. If you have any questions, ideas or you simply want to know a bit more about us, send an e-mail to warp@ambiverse.pl. We'll try to respond to every e-mail we get.
 

  Summing it up We hope we were able to share at least a fraction of our vision. Now we can't do much more than to promise you that we will do everything in our power to provide you with a great, enjoyable game that will meet your expectations. If everything goes as we plan, we will release the game this year. Of course, there might be delays if something unexpected happens. We will regularly update you on the status of development and add new materials on our site.  Keep in touch!
